1
00:00:11,663 --> 00:00:13,657
Mr. Norris,
I'm gonna let one of my guys

2
00:00:13,725 --> 00:00:15,122
show you the Lamborghini.

3
00:00:15,190 --> 00:00:17,753
It's your new car.
You just don't know it yet.

4
00:00:17,820 --> 00:00:20,252
The McLaren looks good on you, Mr. Landau.
Not tonight.

5
00:00:20,319 --> 00:00:22,251
A lot of fellas out there--

6
00:00:22,352 --> 00:00:24,751
They've got to sell
station wagons, minivans,

7
00:00:24,819 --> 00:00:27,351
This?
I don't have to sell this.

8
00:00:27,419 --> 00:00:30,352
This is the good life
on wheels, stem to stern.

9
00:00:30,420 --> 00:00:34,220
Hell, the trunk's bigger
than my first apartment.

10
00:00:34,288 --> 00:00:37,256
Oh, my God.

11
00:00:37,323 --> 00:00:39,590
Liselle.

12
00:00:43,897 --> 00:00:45,831
Agent Rigsby,
what do we have?

13
00:00:45,899 --> 00:00:49,364
Hey, boss. Liselle Douglas,
salesperson here, age 28.

14
00:00:49,432 --> 00:00:51,363
Blunt force trauma,
numerous contusions,

15
00:00:51,431 --> 00:00:53,764
possible skull fracture.
Her clothes are still intact.

16
00:00:53,832 --> 00:00:56,099
No obvious signs
of sexual assault.
oh.

17
00:00:56,166 --> 00:00:59,334
What is it?
I just love that new car smell.

18
00:00:59,402 --> 00:01:00,935
Anything
on the time of death?

19
00:01:00,936 --> 00:01:00,936
She was last seen working here
late last night.

20
00:01:03,003 --> 00:01:06,004
Private security
did a sweep at midnight,

21
00:01:06,071 --> 00:01:07,838
reported the alarm system
hadn't been activated.

22
00:01:07,906 --> 00:01:09,173
Coroner thinks she was
probably dead by then.

23
00:01:09,574 --> 00:01:11,774
Let's get the body out of here,
see what we can find out.

24
00:01:11,841 --> 00:01:12,975
yeah, you got it.

25
00:01:14,376 --> 00:01:15,976
That's expensive, huh?

26
00:01:15,542 --> 00:01:16,942
$300,000 retail.

27
00:01:17,010 --> 00:01:19,177
Probably get
a discount now, though.

28
00:01:24,180 --> 00:01:25,580
Hey, guys.
One of you found the body?

29
00:01:25,648 --> 00:01:28,382
Yeah, James Kinsey. I believe
he's in the john right now.

30
00:01:28,450 --> 00:01:29,585
Brad Elias.

31
00:01:29,586 --> 00:01:31,486
Any idea who could have
done this, Mr. Elias?

32
00:01:31,553 --> 00:01:34,787
No. None. It was horrible.
This is a tragedy.

33
00:01:34,855 --> 00:01:37,557
We're like a family here.
Ha! Family.

34
00:01:37,625 --> 00:01:40,193
That's cute.
Excuse me?

35
00:01:40,260 --> 00:01:42,194
You work on commission,
right?

36
00:01:42,262 --> 00:01:46,061
Sure.
Okay, then you're not a family
at all. You're a gladiator pit.

37
00:01:46,129 --> 00:01:47,591
You're a seething mass

38
00:01:47,659 --> 00:01:49,759
of primal hostility
and mistrust.

39
00:01:49,827 --> 00:01:51,594
That's not true.

40
00:01:51,662 --> 00:01:53,595
People have the wrong idea
about sales.

41
00:01:53,663 --> 00:01:57,398
There's a lot of respect
among us, right, guys?
oh, yeah.

42
00:01:57,466 --> 00:01:58,933
Clearly you're a top dog
amongst this pack here,

43
00:01:59,001 --> 00:02:01,035
But the question is,
who's the fastest runner?

44
00:02:01,636 --> 00:02:03,036
Runner?

45
00:02:03,003 --> 00:02:06,271
Liselle's clients are gonna need
a new broker, aren't they?

46
00:02:06,338 --> 00:02:08,606
And I think that my associate,
agent Cho here,

47
00:02:08,673 --> 00:02:11,374
left her client list upstairs.
In your break room.

48
00:02:11,442 --> 00:02:14,610
It might be a little ghoulish
to grab it up so soon,

49
00:02:14,677 --> 00:02:17,445
but it is still up there,
and someone,

50
00:02:17,513 --> 00:02:20,447
at some point, will...

51
00:02:20,515 --> 00:02:22,949
I've got the client list
right here. It's evidence.

52
00:02:23,017 --> 00:02:24,984
What did you do that for?

53
00:02:25,051 --> 00:02:27,953
I have eliminated this man
from any suspicion.

54
00:02:28,020 --> 00:02:31,155
Too honest to profit from
a killing? Too honest to kill.

55
00:02:31,223 --> 00:02:32,556
Right?
Right.

56
00:02:34,525 --> 00:02:37,593
Hey, guys, break it up.

57
00:02:37,661 --> 00:02:39,594
Unless, of course,
you're very cunning

58
00:02:39,662 --> 00:02:41,196
And you're working
a double bluff.

59
00:02:41,197 --> 00:02:42,197
come on. Take it--
hey, come on.

60
00:02:42,664 --> 00:02:44,598
No, I didn't think so.

61
00:02:44,666 --> 00:02:46,633
come on. Come on.

62
00:02:46,701 --> 00:02:49,235
Come on. Break it up.
Break it up. Come on, guys. Hey.

63
00:02:49,303 --> 00:02:52,237
<font color=#7FFF00>â« The Mentalist 2x13 â«</font>
<font color=#FF0000>Redline</font>
<font color=#FFFF00>Original Air Date on February 4, 2010</font>

64
00:02:52,305 --> 00:02:56,306
-- Sync, corrected by <font color="#00ff00">elderman</font> --
-- for <font color="#ffff00">addicted.com</font> --

65
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:05,307
Liselle didn't show up
for work yesterday.

66
00:03:05,375 --> 00:03:08,344
I didn't know what to think.
It wasn't like her.

67
00:03:08,411 --> 00:03:09,912
You were worried?

68
00:03:09,913 --> 00:03:12,847
I was pissed. Hosting the party
was her responsibility.

69
00:03:12,915 --> 00:03:15,783
It's a good think that
Kinsey stepped up.

70
00:03:15,851 --> 00:03:18,219
Heard you boys
didn't play nice last night.

71
00:03:18,287 --> 00:03:20,187
Naughty, naughty.

72
00:03:20,255 --> 00:03:22,522
You like your employees
at each other's throats?

73
00:03:22,590 --> 00:03:25,191
You bet I do.
This is a job for winners.

74
00:03:25,258 --> 00:03:27,525
We're the top luxury broker
in northern California.

75
00:03:27,593 --> 00:03:29,827
We got four floors of stock
back there.

76
00:03:29,895 --> 00:03:32,463
We got over $100 million
in sales annually.

77
00:03:32,530 --> 00:03:35,731
My guys have to earn
their place.

78
00:03:36,032 --> 00:03:37,732
So every six months
we have a sales drive.

79
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:41,568
So
Top guy on the board gets
a titanium diamond Rolex.

80
00:03:41,635 --> 00:03:44,503
Bottom guy...
gets a new job.

81
00:03:44,571 --> 00:03:47,441
Look, agents,

82
00:03:47,508 --> 00:03:50,611
Not to press--my clients would
like to know when we can reopen.

83
00:03:50,678 --> 00:03:51,547
What can I tell them?

84
00:03:51,548 --> 00:03:52,748
You can tell them
a woman's dead.

85
00:03:54,015 --> 00:03:57,649
Which is terrible, uh,
but this is a service business.

86
00:03:58,217 --> 00:04:01,118
And when sharks stop swimming,
they drown, right?

87
00:04:06,257 --> 00:04:08,191
no malingering guys.

88
00:04:08,259 --> 00:04:10,793
This is James Kinsey.

89
00:04:10,861 --> 00:04:13,128
Ah.

90
00:04:13,196 --> 00:04:15,931
Ah, top salesman.
Congratulations.

91
00:04:15,998 --> 00:04:18,800
Thanks.
Damn right. This guy
could sell a cat to a mouse.

92
00:04:18,867 --> 00:04:23,103
Ah, I might have to throw in
a few extras to close that deal.

93
00:04:23,171 --> 00:04:25,339
Mr. Westhoff here says
you were working with Liselle

94
00:04:25,407 --> 00:04:26,308
the night she disappeared.

95
00:04:26,309 --> 00:04:28,109
Yeah, working
on last night's party, sure.

96
00:04:28,276 --> 00:04:30,411
I left her here
about, uh, 8:00, 8:30.

97
00:04:30,412 --> 00:04:31,812
How'd she seem--her demeanor?

98
00:04:32,278 --> 00:04:34,780
Fine, I guess.
Uh, a little tense, maybe.

99
00:04:34,847 --> 00:04:36,481
A lot of pressure to get
that party together.

100
00:04:36,549 --> 00:04:38,817
Hey. Hey.
That--that's--that's mine.

101
00:04:40,384 --> 00:04:41,851
That.

102
00:04:41,919 --> 00:04:43,653
Okay.

103
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:45,788
Now how'd you and Liselle
get along?

104
00:04:45,856 --> 00:04:48,357
Uh, great.
She's a great girl.

105
00:04:48,425 --> 00:04:49,658
Great?

106
00:04:49,726 --> 00:04:52,194
But you resented her.
No.

107
00:04:52,261 --> 00:04:53,862
Yes.

108
00:04:54,929 --> 00:04:57,498
Why was that? She was
in the middle of the pack,

109
00:04:57,566 --> 00:05:00,000
So she was no threat to you.

110
00:05:00,068 --> 00:05:03,336
Liselle did very well
for her age.

111
00:05:03,404 --> 00:05:06,339
She did very well
because she was beautiful,

112
00:05:06,407 --> 00:05:08,542
And you felt that gave her
an unfair advantage.

113
00:05:08,609 --> 00:05:11,745
hey, sex sells.
That's a fact of life.

114
00:05:11,813 --> 00:05:13,647
Oh, yeah.

115
00:05:13,714 --> 00:05:16,516
Listen, her actual
pitching skills--bush league.

116
00:05:16,584 --> 00:05:19,386
You put a bag on her,
Liselle couldn't sell squat.

117
00:05:19,454 --> 00:05:22,255
Ever ask her out?
Yeah.

118
00:05:22,323 --> 00:05:24,424
How'd that go for you?

119
00:05:24,492 --> 00:05:26,160
Uh, she said no. Boyfriend.

120
00:05:26,328 --> 00:05:27,028
What was his name?

121
00:05:27,096 --> 00:05:31,564
Um, uh, Jeff. Jeff somebody--
musician, wannabe rock star.

122
00:05:31,932 --> 00:05:33,866
Yeah, she was
always bitching about him.

123
00:05:33,934 --> 00:05:35,568
Always drama with those two.

124
00:05:37,137 --> 00:05:39,171
Boyfriend is Jeff Sparhawk.

125
00:05:39,239 --> 00:05:40,440
The victim had a loft with him
south of Market.

126
00:05:40,508 --> 00:05:43,375
Here's the address.
Jane and I will look into it.

127
00:05:43,443 --> 00:05:44,411
You check
out her financials.

128
00:05:44,412 --> 00:05:46,212
You wanted to see me, boss?

129
00:05:47,078 --> 00:05:50,281
Actually, I wanted to see both
of you. Shut the door. Sit down.

130
00:06:00,356 --> 00:06:02,557
You know what this is about.

131
00:06:02,625 --> 00:06:04,494
The other day you told me
you were involved

132
00:06:04,561 --> 00:06:06,597
in a romantic relationship
with each other.

133
00:06:06,598 --> 00:06:07,598
Yes.

134
00:06:09,465 --> 00:06:10,700
Dating within the unit is

135
00:06:10,767 --> 00:06:13,803
strictly against
CBI regulations.

136
00:06:13,871 --> 00:06:17,140
I wanted to take some time
to think about how to respond,

137
00:06:17,208 --> 00:06:19,644
but I realize
that it's causing tension, so...

138
00:06:23,879 --> 00:06:26,114
Agent Rigsby and Van Pelt,

139
00:06:26,182 --> 00:06:29,317
are you involved in a personal
relationship with each other?

140
00:06:29,985 --> 00:06:32,386
Yes.
We are.

141
00:06:32,453 --> 00:06:33,987
Okay, then.

142
00:06:34,055 --> 00:06:36,990
As your supervisor, I have
to report the relationship

143
00:06:37,058 --> 00:06:39,392
to employee support services.
I'm gonna do it

144
00:06:39,460 --> 00:06:41,661
as soon as
we close this case.

145
00:06:41,729 --> 00:06:44,431
Do you have any questions?

146
00:06:44,498 --> 00:06:48,133
But they'll make one of us
transfer out of the unit.

147
00:06:48,201 --> 00:06:50,135
Yes, they will.

148
00:06:50,203 --> 00:06:52,171
That's the rule.
You knew that.

149
00:06:56,677 --> 00:06:58,846
You can go now.

150
00:07:08,856 --> 00:07:11,322
Where the hell is 4-B?

151
00:07:11,390 --> 00:07:13,321
I understand your position.

152
00:07:13,389 --> 00:07:14,985
There's no need
to beat yourself up about it.

153
00:07:14,986 --> 00:07:16,186
What are you talking about?

154
00:07:16,553 --> 00:07:18,416
Well, that you feel bad
about Rigsby and Van Pelt.

155
00:07:18,417 --> 00:07:19,417
No, I don't.

156
00:07:20,184 --> 00:07:21,117
Well,
you can't help wondering

157
00:07:21,185 --> 00:07:23,987
If there's a hint of jealousy
and resentment in your decision.

158
00:07:23,988 --> 00:07:24,988
Excuse me?

159
00:07:27,857 --> 00:07:29,190
Ah.

160
00:07:32,362 --> 00:07:35,264
Mr. Sparhawk?

161
00:07:35,332 --> 00:07:38,501
We're with the California
Bureau of Investigation.

162
00:07:40,070 --> 00:07:42,538
California what?

163
00:07:42,606 --> 00:07:46,709
We want to ask you
some questions about Liselle.

164
00:07:46,777 --> 00:07:49,879
You want to put down
what's left of your guitar?

165
00:07:49,947 --> 00:07:52,615
Yeah. Whatever.

166
00:07:54,218 --> 00:07:57,120
I'll make some tea.

167
00:07:59,390 --> 00:08:01,325
Why all the demolition,
Jeff?

168
00:08:01,392 --> 00:08:04,395
I'm sad. I like
to destroy things when I'm sad.

169
00:08:04,463 --> 00:08:07,832
Well, some sadness,
but mostly guilt,

170
00:08:07,900 --> 00:08:10,202
A dollop of self-pity,

171
00:08:10,269 --> 00:08:12,636
Tingle of excitement.

172
00:08:12,704 --> 00:08:16,306
So you're a musician?

173
00:08:16,374 --> 00:08:18,207
All right.

174
00:08:18,275 --> 00:08:19,742
You any good?

175
00:08:19,810 --> 00:08:21,711
No.

176
00:08:21,779 --> 00:08:24,713
You're okay. I could tell
Liselle was a woman of taste.

177
00:08:24,781 --> 00:08:26,815
She wouldn't have loved
a bad musician.

178
00:08:26,883 --> 00:08:28,216
Yeah.

179
00:08:28,283 --> 00:08:30,351
I'm great. Huge.

180
00:08:30,418 --> 00:08:33,486
Last year I made $9,000
for my music.

181
00:08:33,554 --> 00:08:36,388
Well, that's $9,000 more than
van Gogh ever made from his art.

182
00:08:37,957 --> 00:08:39,924
Yeah,
things worked out for him.

183
00:08:39,992 --> 00:08:42,526
Okay. So, um, Liselle
was the breadwinner?

184
00:08:42,593 --> 00:08:45,228
Yeah. Her cut on an Aston...

185
00:08:45,296 --> 00:08:47,264
could keep us going
for a couple months,

186
00:08:47,331 --> 00:08:50,099
So I could concentrate
on my music.

187
00:08:50,167 --> 00:08:52,668
She did it for me.
She hated that job.

188
00:08:52,736 --> 00:08:54,770
Did that ever cause tension
in your relationship?

189
00:08:54,838 --> 00:08:56,538
Sure.

190
00:08:56,606 --> 00:08:58,573
Couples fight.

191
00:08:58,641 --> 00:09:00,909
I didn't like her working
at that place, but...

192
00:09:00,977 --> 00:09:04,011
You needed the money.
It's fair enough.

193
00:09:04,079 --> 00:09:06,914
She was getting hit on
all the time

194
00:09:06,982 --> 00:09:09,881
by rich egomaniacs, okay?

195
00:09:09,949 --> 00:09:11,882
It's gonna make you jealous,
right?

196
00:09:11,950 --> 00:09:12,717
Guys, uh,
guys try to give her stuff.

197
00:09:12,718 --> 00:09:13,718
What kind of stuff?

198
00:09:14,485 --> 00:09:17,853
You know,
uh, jewelry, perfume,

199
00:09:17,921 --> 00:09:21,589
Stuff like that.
Liselle always sent it back.

200
00:09:21,657 --> 00:09:24,759
Why?
Out of respect for me.

201
00:09:24,826 --> 00:09:26,162
Or if she couldn't give it back,
she gave it away.

202
00:09:26,963 --> 00:09:28,163
Not all of it.

203
00:09:30,965 --> 00:09:34,433
This is very valuable.

204
00:09:34,501 --> 00:09:38,303
Liselle said it was
too valuable to get rid of.

205
00:09:38,370 --> 00:09:41,372
She said we'd use it to, uh,
pay for our wedding.

206
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:44,441
Who gave her the print?

207
00:09:44,509 --> 00:09:47,944
I've done bad,
stupid things.

208
00:09:48,012 --> 00:09:50,446
I never deserved her.

209
00:09:50,513 --> 00:09:52,413
And now she's gone. God.

210
00:09:52,481 --> 00:09:54,082
Oh, stop.

211
00:09:54,149 --> 00:09:56,116
Self-pity'll kill you.

212
00:09:57,886 --> 00:10:00,788
Take it from someone that knows.

213
00:10:00,855 --> 00:10:03,022
Jeff Sparhawk
has no alibi.

214
00:10:03,090 --> 00:10:05,324
You can dispense
with the cop talk, Lisbon.

215
00:10:05,391 --> 00:10:06,125
You can tell me
what's bothering you.

216
00:10:06,126 --> 00:10:07,326
Nothing's bothering me.

217
00:10:07,593 --> 00:10:10,794
Okay.
Nothing is bothering me.

218
00:10:10,862 --> 00:10:13,095
Message received.
Good.

219
00:10:13,163 --> 00:10:15,197
Sparhawk--no alibi, yeah?

220
00:10:15,264 --> 00:10:16,898
Mm.

221
00:10:16,966 --> 00:10:18,899
okay,

222
00:10:18,967 --> 00:10:20,901
I'm jealous and resentful?

223
00:10:20,968 --> 00:10:22,402
That is nonsense.

224
00:10:22,470 --> 00:10:24,970
yet you recall
my exact words.

225
00:10:25,038 --> 00:10:28,506
There's no shame in it. I feel
that way, too, sometimes.

226
00:10:28,574 --> 00:10:31,508
Why does everyone else
get to have a normal life?

227
00:10:31,576 --> 00:10:33,110
My life is fine.

228
00:10:33,177 --> 00:10:35,645
Normally you rise above
such craven emotions,

229
00:10:35,712 --> 00:10:38,180
but in this case,
your hands were tied.

230
00:10:38,247 --> 00:10:40,181
It's the rules.
You're forced to do

231
00:10:40,248 --> 00:10:43,183
what your worst self is
telling you to do anyway.

232
00:10:43,250 --> 00:10:45,284
Hence, your tension headache.

233
00:10:45,352 --> 00:10:48,187
I don't...

234
00:10:48,254 --> 00:10:49,954
All right.

235
00:10:50,022 --> 00:10:52,456
I-I do have a headache,
but that's a coincidence.

236
00:10:52,524 --> 00:10:54,091
Nah.

237
00:10:54,159 --> 00:10:56,093
Either I obey the rules

238
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:58,461
or I risk taking big heat
for ignoring them.

239
00:10:58,529 --> 00:11:00,497
This is on Van Pelt
and Rigsby, not me.

240
00:11:00,498 --> 00:11:01,498
Whatever you say.

241
00:11:01,665 --> 00:11:04,566
Lisbon.

242
00:11:04,633 --> 00:11:07,272
Hey, I found
something on that print.

243
00:11:07,340 --> 00:11:10,175
It sold at auction
in San Francisco last year,

244
00:11:10,243 --> 00:11:13,248
purchased by Walter Mashburn
for 30 grand.

245
00:11:13,318 --> 00:11:15,556
Mashburn. Sounds familiar.

246
00:11:15,623 --> 00:11:17,694
He founded Mashburn Avionics,

247
00:11:17,762 --> 00:11:19,698
sold it ten years ago
for billions.

248
00:11:19,766 --> 00:11:21,700
He was also Liselle Douglas'
last appointment

249
00:11:21,767 --> 00:11:23,301
the day she died.

250
00:11:26,539 --> 00:11:29,474
Did you notice the badge,
or should I show you again?

251
00:11:29,542 --> 00:11:33,009
I'm so sorry, but I can't say
if Mr. Mashburn is here or not.

252
00:11:33,077 --> 00:11:36,312
We're a private club, and our
members treasure their privacy.

253
00:11:36,380 --> 00:11:38,214
Don't worry.
I'll find him.

254
00:11:41,317 --> 00:11:43,752
W--excuse me, sir.

255
00:11:47,757 --> 00:11:50,859
Well, hello there.

256
00:11:50,927 --> 00:11:52,728
The deck, corner table?

257
00:11:52,795 --> 00:11:54,696
Huh?

258
00:11:54,763 --> 00:11:57,197
Oh, you must be new.
Walter Mashburn.

259
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:01,800
I liked Liselle.

260
00:12:01,868 --> 00:12:03,535
Smart woman. Damn shame.

261
00:12:03,603 --> 00:12:05,937
And you gave her
an expensive gift.

262
00:12:06,005 --> 00:12:08,906
Yes.
Were you sleeping with her?

263
00:12:08,974 --> 00:12:12,241
If I slept
with everyone I gave gifts to,

264
00:12:12,308 --> 00:12:14,742
I wouldn't get
any work done...

265
00:12:14,810 --> 00:12:16,046
or any sleep,
for that matter.

266
00:12:16,847 --> 00:12:18,947
But you propositioned her,
and she said no.

267
00:12:21,148 --> 00:12:22,682
Perceptive.

268
00:12:25,352 --> 00:12:27,286
You're a psychic,
aren't you?

269
00:12:27,354 --> 00:12:29,956
What makes you say that?

270
00:12:30,023 --> 00:12:31,957
You have this charlatan air
about you.

271
00:12:33,293 --> 00:12:35,427
My second...

272
00:12:35,495 --> 00:12:38,865
no, my third wife was into
all that mystical goop.

273
00:12:38,932 --> 00:12:42,101
Mm-hmm.
You learn to recognize the type.

274
00:12:42,168 --> 00:12:44,802
How many wives have you had?

275
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:46,804
enough to know better.

276
00:12:46,872 --> 00:12:48,739
But I'm currently
unattached.

277
00:12:51,976 --> 00:12:55,945
So were you sleeping
with Liselle or not?

278
00:12:56,012 --> 00:12:58,646
Not.

279
00:12:58,714 --> 00:13:00,648
That print was a reward

280
00:13:00,716 --> 00:13:03,584
for finding me an Austin Healey
2-seater from 1960.

281
00:13:03,651 --> 00:13:04,454
There was
only a few hundred made.
Mm-hmm.

282
00:13:04,521 --> 00:13:05,724
No. She earned that gift.

283
00:13:06,125 --> 00:13:08,225
And the appointment you had
with her the day she died?

284
00:13:08,392 --> 00:13:09,327
To pick the car up.

285
00:13:09,328 --> 00:13:10,428
Do you want to see it?

286
00:13:10,429 --> 00:13:11,129
No, thanks.

287
00:13:11,195 --> 00:13:12,762
I'd love to.

288
00:13:14,663 --> 00:13:17,999
You have a damaged intensity
that's quite attractive.

289
00:13:18,066 --> 00:13:19,267
Mm. Yeah.

290
00:13:19,335 --> 00:13:20,570
Let me buy you
a drink sometime.

291
00:13:20,571 --> 00:13:22,071
I live in Sacramento.

292
00:13:22,138 --> 00:13:23,106
I have a jet.

293
00:13:23,107 --> 00:13:25,507
Oh, you're very good.
Very good.

294
00:13:26,574 --> 00:13:30,075
I have one question--
uh, did you kill Liselle?

295
00:13:31,911 --> 00:13:34,179
Hmm?

296
00:13:34,247 --> 00:13:37,815
Jake, check, please.

297
00:13:37,883 --> 00:13:39,917
Let me show you folks
something.

298
00:13:39,985 --> 00:13:43,921
Smugglers call 'em
go-fast boats--says it all.

299
00:13:43,989 --> 00:13:46,823
Nothing like flying
across the ocean at 80 knots

300
00:13:46,891 --> 00:13:48,324
to get the blood going.

301
00:13:48,392 --> 00:13:50,693
Would you like
to come for a ride?

302
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:52,928
We get it.
You're an energetic man.

303
00:13:52,995 --> 00:13:55,830
You like danger.
So why bring us here?

304
00:13:55,898 --> 00:13:57,565
I have no love for danger.

305
00:13:57,632 --> 00:14:00,534
Nothing's dangerous
if you think ahead.

306
00:14:00,602 --> 00:14:03,203
If you plan it right,
you can get away with...

307
00:14:03,271 --> 00:14:06,639
Well, I was gonna say you can
get away with murder, but...

308
00:14:06,707 --> 00:14:09,975
you know what I mean.

309
00:14:10,043 --> 00:14:11,477
Okay. So...

310
00:14:11,544 --> 00:14:14,980
What's the point in showing us
your fancy toy here?

311
00:14:15,047 --> 00:14:18,816
This is how I live my life.
I have a Castle in Scotland,

312
00:14:18,884 --> 00:14:21,585
A compound on the waterfront
in Marin.

313
00:14:21,652 --> 00:14:24,554
If I killed Liselle,
would I stuff her in the trunk

314
00:14:24,621 --> 00:14:28,124
like some low-rent thug?
How would you have done it?

315
00:14:28,191 --> 00:14:30,159
She would have
just disappeared,

316
00:14:30,227 --> 00:14:33,528
Like smoke,
like she was never there.

317
00:14:33,596 --> 00:14:36,631
You enjoy being
a murder suspect, don't you?

318
00:14:36,699 --> 00:14:39,299
Am I? A suspect?

319
00:14:39,367 --> 00:14:42,002
Of course. It could be
you're a sociopath,

320
00:14:42,069 --> 00:14:45,071
or it could be that killing is
a thrill that you can't buy.

321
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:49,175
Not a lot excites you anymore,
does it, Walter?

322
00:14:49,243 --> 00:14:52,912
Patrick, if you really think
I killed Liselle,

323
00:14:52,980 --> 00:14:56,482
there's only one thing
for you to do.

324
00:14:56,550 --> 00:14:59,485
Try and catch me.

325
00:15:12,429 --> 00:15:14,363
That could be you.

326
00:15:20,381 --> 00:15:23,116
Mashburn's got zero priors,
but he's been investigated

327
00:15:23,184 --> 00:15:24,653
For several
shady business deals.

328
00:15:24,654 --> 00:15:25,454
But they never found
anything.

329
00:15:25,521 --> 00:15:27,156
Legit business genius,
it says here.

330
00:15:27,157 --> 00:15:29,957
He thinks he's a genius.
He's a pirate that got lucky.

331
00:15:30,024 --> 00:15:32,626
He's gotten everything he wanted
since he was 30 years old.

332
00:15:32,627 --> 00:15:33,627
Except you.

333
00:15:33,893 --> 00:15:35,827
Wait. Walter Mashburn
asked you out?

334
00:15:35,895 --> 00:15:37,528
No.

335
00:15:39,131 --> 00:15:41,831
Well, sort of.
Wow.

336
00:15:41,899 --> 00:15:44,001
Personally, I thought
she should have gone for it.

337
00:15:44,069 --> 00:15:46,670
A little empty glamour
would have been good for her.

338
00:15:46,738 --> 00:15:47,872
But, no, not our Lisbon.

339
00:15:48,873 --> 00:15:49,773
Rigsby, why don't you go

340
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:52,642
and talk to his alibi,
the swimsuit model?

341
00:15:52,709 --> 00:15:56,045
Oh, sure, yeah, the swimsuit
model. Uh, no problem.

342
00:15:56,113 --> 00:15:57,746
The alibi will be solid,
whether he did it or not.

343
00:15:57,814 --> 00:15:59,914
Check anyway.
I got something.

344
00:15:59,982 --> 00:16:02,550
It seems Westhoff,
the boss at Zenith Motors,

345
00:16:02,617 --> 00:16:04,118
reported a Ferrari disappeared
from their service department

346
00:16:04,186 --> 00:16:05,921
the night of the murder.
But an hour later,

347
00:16:05,988 --> 00:16:07,691
Westhoff called the sheriff back
and said never mind.

348
00:16:07,792 --> 00:16:08,792
So he found the car?

349
00:16:08,858 --> 00:16:09,893
Didn't say.

350
00:16:09,894 --> 00:16:11,094
We need to find out.

351
00:16:11,195 --> 00:16:12,795
I got the autopsy report.

352
00:16:13,461 --> 00:16:15,429
Liselle died
of major head trauma

353
00:16:15,496 --> 00:16:17,430
caused by forceful contact
with the pavement.

354
00:16:17,498 --> 00:16:19,895
That put together with
skin abrasions, bone fractures--

355
00:16:19,963 --> 00:16:21,592
She was hit by a car.

356
00:16:21,593 --> 00:16:22,893
Well, if a car is
the murder weapon,

357
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:25,094
it'll have trace evidence
on it--blood, D.N.A.--

358
00:16:25,162 --> 00:16:26,095
Even if the killer washed it.

359
00:16:26,163 --> 00:16:29,831
Talk to Westhoff. D.N.A.
evidence doesn't last forever.
Okay.

360
00:16:29,899 --> 00:16:32,600
Whoo.

361
00:16:34,669 --> 00:16:36,636
I'm out sick two days,

362
00:16:36,737 --> 00:16:38,106
and you give the Tarlen account
to Legler?

363
00:16:38,107 --> 00:16:40,407
You've been sick on and off
for a month.

364
00:16:40,473 --> 00:16:42,008
It's not my fault
I got a stomach bug.

365
00:16:42,009 --> 00:16:43,109
Hey, no free rides.

366
00:16:43,175 --> 00:16:45,244
You eat what you kill here--
that's rule number one.

367
00:16:45,245 --> 00:16:46,445
Don't tell me about rules,
you son of a bitch.

368
00:16:46,512 --> 00:16:48,779
This is me talking.
Oh, you?

369
00:16:48,847 --> 00:16:51,715
Yeah.
You need to remember which one
of us here is the man.

370
00:16:51,783 --> 00:16:54,851
Hey, guys.
Are we interrupting something?

371
00:16:57,687 --> 00:16:59,955
Management seminar.

372
00:17:00,023 --> 00:17:01,723
Traditionally
in these dominance displays,

373
00:17:01,791 --> 00:17:05,393
it's customary to, uh,
bare one's canines.

374
00:17:07,296 --> 00:17:11,131
Some species go so far as
exposing their genitals. Yeah?

375
00:17:11,199 --> 00:17:15,035
1986 Ferrari Testarossa--
belongs to an Alexa Landau,

376
00:17:15,102 --> 00:17:18,072
And it disappeared from your
service department. Where is it?

377
00:17:18,073 --> 00:17:19,073
I don't know.

378
00:17:19,139 --> 00:17:20,576
Then why'd you tell the cops
"never mind"?

379
00:17:21,577 --> 00:17:23,777
'cause I told him the owner's
husband may have taken the car.

380
00:17:23,643 --> 00:17:26,145
We try not to call the police
on our clients.

381
00:17:26,146 --> 00:17:27,546
He stole
his own wife's car?

382
00:17:27,613 --> 00:17:29,547
Yeah,
Landaus are splitting up.

383
00:17:29,615 --> 00:17:32,416
You know, rich people and their
frickin' soap opera lives.

384
00:17:32,483 --> 00:17:35,585
Apparently, the husband took
the car to Vegas, partied hard,

385
00:17:35,652 --> 00:17:37,254
left the car a mess.
Now Alexa's pissed.

386
00:17:37,255 --> 00:17:39,055
And before she jets off
to Milan,

387
00:17:39,122 --> 00:17:40,490
she brings it in
to be detailed,

388
00:17:40,558 --> 00:17:44,161
Specifically tells Kinsey not
to let her pig husband near it.

389
00:17:44,828 --> 00:17:45,963
He tells me this later.

390
00:17:45,964 --> 00:17:48,464
And you think the husband
didn't take no for an answer?

391
00:17:49,331 --> 00:17:50,931
Noah Landau's
a big record producer,

392
00:17:51,099 --> 00:17:53,800
not really known for his impulse
control. And he loves that car.

393
00:17:54,001 --> 00:17:55,801
Noah Landau was
at the cocktail party

394
00:17:55,867 --> 00:17:58,102
when Liselle's body was
discovered. I'll talk to Lisbon.

395
00:17:58,570 --> 00:18:02,004
Mm. "rich people and their
frickin' soap opera lives."

396
00:18:02,072 --> 00:18:03,974
You don't really like rich
people much, do you, Kinsey?

397
00:18:03,975 --> 00:18:05,475
Are you kidding?
I love 'em.

398
00:18:06,542 --> 00:18:09,210
I'm on the way up, my friend.
Rich people are taking me there.

399
00:18:09,277 --> 00:18:11,178
Well, someday,
but in the meantime,

400
00:18:11,245 --> 00:18:13,913
Landau is dining at some
lavish restaurant in Las Vegas.

401
00:18:13,981 --> 00:18:15,614
Sitting across the table

402
00:18:15,682 --> 00:18:17,616
from him is a woman
probably half his age

403
00:18:17,684 --> 00:18:20,018
that's laughing
at every one of his jokes.

404
00:18:20,086 --> 00:18:23,321
And you're stuck here with this
guy, reheating... Beef soup?

405
00:18:23,389 --> 00:18:27,458
Beef--beef barley.
Do you mind?
Sure.

406
00:18:27,526 --> 00:18:30,827
Would you say
you have food issues?

407
00:18:30,895 --> 00:18:33,831
You don't have to answer that.
Were you an orphan?

408
00:18:33,899 --> 00:18:36,633
A lot of thieves around here.

409
00:18:36,701 --> 00:18:39,635
Oh, like I'm gonna steal
your lunch.
Well, someone did.

410
00:18:39,703 --> 00:18:42,037
Yeah, just the other day.
How low is that?

411
00:18:42,105 --> 00:18:45,006
Beef barley?
Yeah.

412
00:18:45,074 --> 00:18:46,674
Beef--

413
00:18:46,742 --> 00:18:49,543
It's not really
a popular soup meat, is it?

414
00:18:49,611 --> 00:18:52,179
Each his own.

415
00:18:52,246 --> 00:18:53,646
Yeah, I guess.

416
00:18:53,714 --> 00:18:56,650
So he killed her
while stealing his own car?

417
00:18:56,717 --> 00:18:59,052
That's the theory.
Look, Grace,

418
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:01,054
I just wanna let you know
I'm not worried

419
00:19:01,121 --> 00:19:03,290
about Lisbon reporting us. We'll
make it work, whatever happens.

420
00:19:03,291 --> 00:19:04,091
I know we will.

421
00:19:04,157 --> 00:19:05,092
If worse comes to worse,

422
00:19:05,159 --> 00:19:07,394
they probably wouldn't transfer
you out of the central valley.

423
00:19:07,562 --> 00:19:09,097
L.A. or something like that
is really unlikely.

424
00:19:09,098 --> 00:19:11,198
We'll you're assuming
I'm the one to be transferred?

425
00:19:12,164 --> 00:19:13,932
Yeah, I've been here
almost five years, so seniority,

426
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:15,335
Plus, this is my career,
you know?

427
00:19:15,436 --> 00:19:17,436
It's my career, too, Wayne.

428
00:19:17,502 --> 00:19:18,436
No,
I didn't mean it that way.

429
00:19:18,504 --> 00:19:19,806
Obviously, you can have
a career as well.

430
00:19:20,407 --> 00:19:21,807
Thanks for your permission.

431
00:19:27,609 --> 00:19:28,978
Why would I steal
my own car?

432
00:19:28,979 --> 00:19:29,979
Oh, it was your wife's car,
Mr. Landau,

433
00:19:30,046 --> 00:19:32,014
Your, uh, estranged wife?

434
00:19:32,081 --> 00:19:35,217
Yeah, well, we're uh--
what do you call--reconciling.

435
00:19:35,284 --> 00:19:37,019
Oh? Congratulations.

436
00:19:37,086 --> 00:19:38,720
That's nice.

437
00:19:38,788 --> 00:19:42,758
So the trip to vegas
was a last hurrah?

438
00:19:42,825 --> 00:19:46,328
Yes, we know about it.
We know everything, Mr. Landau.

439
00:19:46,396 --> 00:19:49,264
Liselle Douglas sold your wife
that car. You know her?

440
00:19:49,332 --> 00:19:52,567
Really?
Liselle sold <i>me</i> that car.

441
00:19:52,635 --> 00:19:55,336
'86 Testarossa--
frickin' classic.

442
00:19:55,404 --> 00:19:58,872
You think Alexa even cared?
She can't even drive stick.

443
00:19:58,940 --> 00:20:01,375
So you took what was yours.
That's understandable.

444
00:20:01,442 --> 00:20:03,610
You know what?

445
00:20:03,677 --> 00:20:05,978
You should leave.
You killed her, didn't you?

446
00:20:06,046 --> 00:20:08,616
Ran Liselle down when she
caught you taking the car.

447
00:20:08,617 --> 00:20:10,217
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Wait a second. Wait a second.

448
00:20:10,283 --> 00:20:12,218
That's how she died?

449
00:20:12,219 --> 00:20:13,719
Well, maybe you didn't see her
until it was too late.

450
00:20:13,786 --> 00:20:17,757
It was dark. Help yourself,
Mr. Landau. Tell us your side.

451
00:20:17,825 --> 00:20:19,461
Wow.

452
00:20:19,529 --> 00:20:21,568
Oh, man,
it's not like that.

453
00:20:21,636 --> 00:20:24,605
It's not like that. Look...

454
00:20:24,673 --> 00:20:28,108
When I got back
from Vegas,

455
00:20:28,176 --> 00:20:29,576
I, uh,

456
00:20:29,644 --> 00:20:34,082
I-I forgot some, uh,
stuff in my car.

457
00:20:34,149 --> 00:20:35,416
Drugs?

458
00:20:35,484 --> 00:20:38,220
No. Yeah, drugs. What else?

459
00:20:38,287 --> 00:20:40,556
Alexa and I--

460
00:20:40,624 --> 00:20:42,892
We're working out
custody of our son.

461
00:20:42,959 --> 00:20:46,596
So you could see how a drug bust
could look bad.

462
00:20:46,597 --> 00:20:47,497
Well, a place like Zenith

463
00:20:47,564 --> 00:20:49,167
would never call the police
on a client.

464
00:20:49,168 --> 00:20:51,568
Of course not. They'd politely
leave it in the glove box,

465
00:20:51,835 --> 00:20:54,403
where Alexa would find it
and have me thrown in prison.

466
00:20:54,471 --> 00:20:57,307
That's why I had to get the car
before she found the dope.

467
00:20:57,374 --> 00:20:59,676
So you stole it.

468
00:20:59,743 --> 00:21:02,779
Uh, no. I asked someone
to do me a favor.

469
00:21:02,847 --> 00:21:05,181
And then I was partying,
I lost my phone,

470
00:21:05,249 --> 00:21:07,350
I can't get ahold of the guy.

471
00:21:07,417 --> 00:21:09,518
That's why I went
to that stupid cocktail party,

472
00:21:09,586 --> 00:21:11,587
to try to hook up with him.
He's a salesman?

473
00:21:11,655 --> 00:21:13,589
No, no.
It's Liselle's boyfriend.

474
00:21:13,657 --> 00:21:17,260
His name is Jeff Sparhawk.
He's got the car.

475
00:21:17,328 --> 00:21:20,731
Jumped at the chance
to get close to me, so I was...

476
00:21:22,534 --> 00:21:26,504
should have just asked him
to kill my wife.

477
00:21:26,572 --> 00:21:29,807
That's a joke.

478
00:21:31,309 --> 00:21:33,678
You guys, man.

479
00:21:33,745 --> 00:21:35,346
Ooh.

480
00:21:39,185 --> 00:21:40,552
Whoa!

481
00:21:40,620 --> 00:21:43,121
Excuse me. Mr. Jane.

482
00:21:43,188 --> 00:21:44,822
What? Oh, sorry.

483
00:21:44,889 --> 00:21:47,155
If you could just--
right over here.

484
00:21:47,223 --> 00:21:51,155
I'm sorry, Mr. Jane. You cannot
hang out in the merchandise.

485
00:21:51,222 --> 00:21:54,991
Oh. Okay. Uh, well, what we need
then is a test drive.

486
00:21:55,058 --> 00:21:57,226
Down to the beach
would be good.

487
00:21:57,294 --> 00:21:58,695
You're looking to buy?

488
00:21:58,696 --> 00:22:00,696
Absolutely.
Well, not me, but, uh--

489
00:22:00,762 --> 00:22:02,697
I don't really care
for this kind of ostentation,

490
00:22:02,764 --> 00:22:04,698
but Cho likes
what you're cooking.

491
00:22:04,766 --> 00:22:06,501
Do you think you could show us
around the lot?

492
00:22:06,602 --> 00:22:07,702
You know, I'm so sorry.

493
00:22:07,769 --> 00:22:10,404
Our inventory starts in
the low six figures, so I need

494
00:22:10,472 --> 00:22:12,639
a bank statement before
I can book an appointment.

495
00:22:12,707 --> 00:22:16,441
Otherwise we would be inundated
with requests. You understand.

496
00:22:16,509 --> 00:22:17,842
Yeah, of course.

497
00:22:17,910 --> 00:22:19,912
Uh, you'd make an exception
for a friend, wouldn't you?

498
00:22:20,913 --> 00:22:21,913
No.

499
00:22:22,780 --> 00:22:24,213
Oh. Okay.

500
00:22:24,281 --> 00:22:26,916
Hey. We got a lead on Sparhawk
and the missing Ferrari.

501
00:22:26,984 --> 00:22:28,217
Gotta go.
Uh, could you do me a favor?

502
00:22:28,285 --> 00:22:29,920
Could you drop me someplace
on the way?

503
00:22:29,921 --> 00:22:30,921
Sure.

504
00:22:46,298 --> 00:22:47,499
Patrick.

505
00:22:47,567 --> 00:22:50,102
Ahoy!

506
00:22:55,539 --> 00:22:56,673
Unexpected pleasure.

507
00:22:56,741 --> 00:22:58,308
What brings you here?

508
00:22:58,375 --> 00:22:59,775
Fishing.

509
00:22:59,843 --> 00:23:01,244
For what?

510
00:23:01,311 --> 00:23:03,078
Whatever bites.

511
00:23:03,146 --> 00:23:06,047
You're not
on stakeout then?

512
00:23:06,115 --> 00:23:09,284
What's a stakeout?

513
00:23:13,288 --> 00:23:14,756
There's our car.

514
00:23:14,823 --> 00:23:16,357
Where's Sparhawk?

515
00:23:16,425 --> 00:23:19,360
I can't believe he could walk
away from something like this

516
00:23:19,428 --> 00:23:20,364
in one piece.

517
00:23:20,365 --> 00:23:23,065
That's blood on the air bag.
He was in it, all right.

518
00:23:22,932 --> 00:23:24,366
No brake marks.

519
00:23:24,434 --> 00:23:28,804
He ran directly
into the pole.

520
00:23:28,871 --> 00:23:32,274
Put the sword down now.
Come on. Come and get me!

521
00:23:32,342 --> 00:23:34,877
Watch out. Watch out.
Come on, you bastards!
Come and take me.

522
00:23:34,945 --> 00:23:37,045
Put it down! Put it down.

523
00:23:37,113 --> 00:23:39,481
Go ahead and make me!

524
00:23:44,487 --> 00:23:47,955
Don't shoot him
unless he goes at me for real.

525
00:23:48,023 --> 00:23:49,657
I don't know, boss.

526
00:23:49,724 --> 00:23:51,458
Boss...

527
00:24:00,467 --> 00:24:01,900
Jeff...

528
00:24:04,404 --> 00:24:06,738
We need to talk.

529
00:24:07,739 --> 00:24:08,839
No.

530
00:24:15,639 --> 00:24:17,040
Jeff...

531
00:24:17,107 --> 00:24:20,176
Put that thing down <i>now.</i>

532
00:24:20,243 --> 00:24:23,045
Make me.
go ahead and make me!

533
00:24:23,113 --> 00:24:25,948
Nobody's gonna shoot you,
Jeff...

534
00:24:27,784 --> 00:24:30,352
No matter how badly
you want them to.

535
00:24:39,295 --> 00:24:42,130
I killed her.

536
00:24:42,198 --> 00:24:43,699
I killed Liselle.

537
00:24:43,766 --> 00:24:45,734
Then let's talk about it.

538
00:24:45,802 --> 00:24:49,137
Let us help you, Jeff.

539
00:24:49,205 --> 00:24:51,605
Put down the weapon.

540
00:24:56,978 --> 00:25:00,048
Stand down.

541
00:25:01,684 --> 00:25:04,151
You're under arrest, Jeff.

542
00:25:04,219 --> 00:25:06,153
We're gonna take you
to a doctor,

543
00:25:06,221 --> 00:25:08,323
have him check you out.

544
00:25:09,725 --> 00:25:12,660
Is this it? Is this
how you work your magic?

545
00:25:12,728 --> 00:25:15,630
What magic's that? Oh.

546
00:25:15,698 --> 00:25:17,665
Check out
this little puppy.

547
00:25:17,733 --> 00:25:20,435
That's a keeper.

548
00:25:20,502 --> 00:25:23,437
You think I didn't
check you out?

549
00:25:23,505 --> 00:25:24,939
What'd you find?

550
00:25:25,006 --> 00:25:26,941
Psychic,
just as I called it.

551
00:25:27,042 --> 00:25:28,943
Ah, no such thing
as psychics.

552
00:25:29,011 --> 00:25:32,045
Oh, I know. You're a charlatan,
as I said.

553
00:25:32,113 --> 00:25:34,547
You lost your wife and kid
to a serial killer--

554
00:25:34,614 --> 00:25:36,048
Your fault, you think--

555
00:25:36,115 --> 00:25:38,782
And now you're on this
hopeless quest for redemption,

556
00:25:38,850 --> 00:25:41,017
battling evil and injustice,
right?

557
00:25:41,085 --> 00:25:43,386
Close enough.

558
00:25:43,453 --> 00:25:46,388
You play mind games with people,
you size up their weaknesses

559
00:25:46,456 --> 00:25:47,593
And then you give them the rope
to hang themselves.

560
00:25:47,594 --> 00:25:48,794
Oh, you make it sound so cool.

561
00:25:49,361 --> 00:25:51,796
And as for your work
so far on me,

562
00:25:51,864 --> 00:25:53,298
I guess you think

563
00:25:53,365 --> 00:25:55,933
I'm vain, egotistical
and hate being ignored.

564
00:25:56,001 --> 00:25:58,202
Do you disagree?

565
00:25:58,270 --> 00:26:00,538
No.
It's pretty much accurate.
Huh.

566
00:26:00,606 --> 00:26:05,710
But I'm also cunning, ruthless,
and I hate to lose.

567
00:26:05,778 --> 00:26:09,247
Just the kind of man that would
kill a woman for rejecting him.

568
00:26:09,315 --> 00:26:12,984
Did I?
Well, you knew Liselle was
stuffed in the trunk. How?

569
00:26:13,052 --> 00:26:14,985
I have a lot of friends--

570
00:26:15,053 --> 00:26:16,187
Sheriff's Department,
Mayor's Office.

571
00:26:16,188 --> 00:26:17,188
Did you kill Liselle Douglas?

572
00:26:18,255 --> 00:26:20,022
You tell me.

573
00:26:20,090 --> 00:26:23,025
I'll know soon enough. I just
need to read you a little more,

574
00:26:23,092 --> 00:26:24,862
dig a little deeper into
your psyche, if you don't mind.

575
00:26:24,863 --> 00:26:26,863
Not at all. Dig away.
It'll be fun.

576
00:26:27,230 --> 00:26:29,331
Anything for a thrill.

577
00:26:29,399 --> 00:26:31,299
Yes. Pretty much.

578
00:26:31,367 --> 00:26:33,868
Hello?
We brought in
the victim's boyfriend.

579
00:26:33,936 --> 00:26:36,038
He's looking pretty good
for it.

580
00:26:36,105 --> 00:26:37,176
Wanna come
and have a chat with him?

581
00:26:37,177 --> 00:26:39,077
Yeah, maybe a little later.
I'm kind of busy.

582
00:26:39,244 --> 00:26:41,679
Where are you?
Well, I'm with an admirer of yours,

583
00:26:41,747 --> 00:26:44,248
Who, uh, looks very good
for it as well,

584
00:26:44,316 --> 00:26:47,251
Has "killer"
written all over his face.
Not Mashburn.

585
00:26:47,319 --> 00:26:51,154
Tell her I said hi.
Uh, he said hi.

586
00:26:51,222 --> 00:26:53,656
In there.

587
00:26:53,724 --> 00:26:55,758
Hung up.

588
00:26:59,396 --> 00:27:00,930
Grace.
Yes?

589
00:27:00,997 --> 00:27:04,266
Look, you're giving me
frostbite. Can we talk or what?

590
00:27:04,334 --> 00:27:06,869
Sure. I guess.

591
00:27:09,907 --> 00:27:12,542
Okay, look...

592
00:27:12,609 --> 00:27:15,545
I'm sorry. I wasn't trying
to say that your job

593
00:27:15,612 --> 00:27:17,680
is less important than mine.

594
00:27:17,748 --> 00:27:19,882
I know. It's just...

595
00:27:19,950 --> 00:27:22,385
you're deciding
how my career should go?

596
00:27:22,452 --> 00:27:24,887
Planning my entire life
for me?

597
00:27:24,955 --> 00:27:27,022
It's not like we're married
or anything.

598
00:27:27,090 --> 00:27:29,691
Grace, I get it. You're right.
We're not married.

599
00:27:29,758 --> 00:27:32,993
How stupid would that be,
right?

600
00:27:33,061 --> 00:27:33,997
Stupid?

601
00:27:33,998 --> 00:27:35,898
Yeah, um, we've only been
dating a couple months.

602
00:27:35,964 --> 00:27:37,202
Who knows what's gonna happen?

603
00:27:37,203 --> 00:27:39,703
Well, sure,
but what's stupid about it?

604
00:27:39,870 --> 00:27:41,805
I-I-I-I meant stupid
if we got married today.

605
00:27:41,906 --> 00:27:43,306
But what about tomorrow?

606
00:27:43,873 --> 00:27:45,807
I mean, long-term,
where are we?

607
00:27:45,875 --> 00:27:46,710
Do we have to discuss this
right now?

608
00:27:46,711 --> 00:27:49,311
Yeah, we probably
should have done it

609
00:27:49,378 --> 00:27:50,812
Before we announced
our relationship

610
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:51,649
and I endangered my job.

611
00:27:51,650 --> 00:27:52,650
Well,
my job's on the line, too.

612
00:27:52,717 --> 00:27:55,486
That's not what you said before.
You have seniority, remember?

613
00:27:55,487 --> 00:27:56,987
Look, Grace,
I know you're scared,

614
00:27:57,053 --> 00:27:58,655
but you can't keep blowing
hot and cold on me like this,

615
00:27:58,723 --> 00:27:59,658
Not now.

616
00:27:59,659 --> 00:28:02,659
So what, I should just move
to the Fresno Office

617
00:28:02,726 --> 00:28:03,696
and smile about it?

618
00:28:03,697 --> 00:28:05,997
You know what? Fine.
Do whatever you want, Grace.

619
00:28:16,738 --> 00:28:20,040
Jeff, we've got the lab
rushing the results

620
00:28:20,108 --> 00:28:23,343
on the D.N.A. test
on the bumper of the Ferrari.

621
00:28:23,411 --> 00:28:26,346
Once we find Liselle's blood,
any leverage you had is gone.

622
00:28:26,414 --> 00:28:29,516
You should plead this out now.
You think I killed her?

623
00:28:29,584 --> 00:28:32,486
It helps that you said so
during the standoff.

624
00:28:32,553 --> 00:28:35,222
Right.

625
00:28:35,289 --> 00:28:36,623
What's weird...

626
00:28:36,691 --> 00:28:39,392
I think
if I had killed her,

627
00:28:39,460 --> 00:28:43,696
I'd feel better than I do now.
At least I'd feel in control.

628
00:28:43,764 --> 00:28:45,531
So now you're saying
you didn't do it?

629
00:28:45,599 --> 00:28:47,834
I didn't.

630
00:28:47,901 --> 00:28:49,335
But I did...

631
00:28:49,403 --> 00:28:51,771
Metaphorically.

632
00:28:51,839 --> 00:28:53,773
I killed her
with my selfishness.

633
00:28:53,841 --> 00:28:55,975
This isn't a lyric-writing
workshop, Jeff.

634
00:28:56,043 --> 00:28:58,311
You were there
the night she died.

635
00:28:58,378 --> 00:29:02,648
You stole the car at Landau's
request and stashed it where?

636
00:29:02,716 --> 00:29:04,750
Parking garage?

637
00:29:04,818 --> 00:29:06,252
Yeah.

638
00:29:06,319 --> 00:29:09,255
I thought, uh,
if this guy gives me a break,

639
00:29:09,322 --> 00:29:12,825
I can finally make it,
take care of Liselle for once.

640
00:29:15,228 --> 00:29:18,130
She takes care of me
by working her ass off.

641
00:29:18,198 --> 00:29:20,332
My big idea was
grand theft auto.

642
00:29:20,400 --> 00:29:23,635
Maybe Liselle caught you,
tried to stop you.
No.

643
00:29:23,703 --> 00:29:25,837
Maybe it was an accident.

644
00:29:25,905 --> 00:29:27,306
No.

645
00:29:27,373 --> 00:29:31,043
She w--she never even saw me.
She was working too hard.

646
00:29:33,914 --> 00:29:38,017
I loved her.

647
00:29:38,085 --> 00:29:40,019
If I had killed her,

648
00:29:40,087 --> 00:29:43,322
you wouldn't be talking to me,
'cause I'd be dead, too.

649
00:29:46,993 --> 00:29:50,663
We need Jane.
Yeah.

650
00:29:50,731 --> 00:29:53,899
The human brain is
built in layers--

651
00:29:53,967 --> 00:29:55,401
The homo sapien brain

652
00:29:55,469 --> 00:29:58,404
on top of the caveman
on top of the animal.

653
00:29:58,472 --> 00:30:01,107
Way down, deep below, you will
find the lizard brain.

654
00:30:01,174 --> 00:30:03,509
Lizard--
all action and reaction,

655
00:30:03,577 --> 00:30:05,411
No subtlety.

656
00:30:05,479 --> 00:30:08,447
You cannot train it
to not react.

657
00:30:08,515 --> 00:30:11,584
Then where did I hide the ring?
You're telling me.

658
00:30:12,953 --> 00:30:15,388
All the lizard brain knows
is that something is hidden

659
00:30:15,455 --> 00:30:19,859
and you don't want it found.
You can't hide your reaction.

660
00:30:19,926 --> 00:30:23,128
You're talking a good game,
but I don't see my ring.

661
00:30:23,196 --> 00:30:25,698
I'm listening,
and the ring...

662
00:30:25,765 --> 00:30:28,468
Is...

663
00:30:39,612 --> 00:30:42,081
Excuse me.

664
00:30:42,148 --> 00:30:43,482
Huh.

665
00:30:43,550 --> 00:30:44,917
Thanks.

666
00:30:44,984 --> 00:30:46,452
Cheers.

667
00:30:49,989 --> 00:30:51,657
Thank you.

668
00:30:51,725 --> 00:30:53,926
VoilÃ .

669
00:30:53,994 --> 00:30:55,494
Parlor trick.

670
00:30:55,562 --> 00:30:58,563
Yes, but it gives me
a truer sense of your character.

671
00:30:58,631 --> 00:31:01,400
It's quackery.
You--you disappoint me.

672
00:31:01,467 --> 00:31:04,769
You think you sweat too much,
you have mild dirt phobia,

673
00:31:04,837 --> 00:31:06,972
and you have issues
with your mother.

674
00:31:07,039 --> 00:31:09,008
Who doesn't? Quackery.

675
00:31:09,009 --> 00:31:10,009
If I cared at all
about respect,

676
00:31:10,576 --> 00:31:12,078
I would say that
that is disrespectful.

677
00:31:12,079 --> 00:31:13,079
I just say what I see.

678
00:31:13,746 --> 00:31:14,580
I have to prove you wrong.

679
00:31:14,648 --> 00:31:16,516
Do you have, uh,
a good fast car available?

680
00:31:16,517 --> 00:31:17,517
I do.

681
00:31:18,483 --> 00:31:20,217
Mm.

682
00:31:20,285 --> 00:31:22,220
Jane,
what are you doing?

683
00:31:22,287 --> 00:31:24,355
Cho. Proving a point.
Lisbon with you?

684
00:31:24,423 --> 00:31:27,358
No.
Oh, that's a shame.
She'd enjoy this.

685
00:31:27,426 --> 00:31:28,261
She wants you
back at the office.

686
00:31:28,262 --> 00:31:29,662
No doubt. You ready, Walter?

687
00:31:30,129 --> 00:31:33,065
I think so.
Good. Oh! It's very low.

688
00:31:33,132 --> 00:31:35,701
You nervous?
Of course not.

689
00:31:35,769 --> 00:31:39,338
Well, you should be.
It's a very fancy car.

690
00:31:39,406 --> 00:31:41,440
I don't like the color.

691
00:31:41,508 --> 00:31:44,343
But, uh, what I'm gonna do
is steer

692
00:31:44,410 --> 00:31:46,545
by feeling your reactions.

693
00:31:46,612 --> 00:31:48,713
You play it cool, we crash.

694
00:31:48,781 --> 00:31:52,751
Whatever you do,
do not close your eyes. Okay?

695
00:31:57,156 --> 00:31:58,589
Okay. All right.

696
00:31:58,657 --> 00:32:00,591
Uh, how do I turn it on?

697
00:32:00,659 --> 00:32:02,393
Here.
Okay.

698
00:32:02,461 --> 00:32:05,096
whoa.

699
00:32:40,131 --> 00:32:42,098
Whoa!

700
00:32:42,166 --> 00:32:45,068
Whoo!
Oh, I'll be damned.

701
00:32:45,135 --> 00:32:49,037
Ahh! That was fun.

702
00:32:49,105 --> 00:32:52,173
Whoo!

703
00:32:52,241 --> 00:32:55,243
Thank you. VoilÃ .
All in the wrist.

704
00:32:55,310 --> 00:32:57,245
Huh? All in the wrist.

705
00:33:00,715 --> 00:33:02,416
Aah! Ohh!

706
00:33:19,197 --> 00:33:22,032
Why'd you do that?

707
00:33:22,099 --> 00:33:23,866
It was a total accident.

708
00:33:23,934 --> 00:33:28,003
Ah.

709
00:33:28,071 --> 00:33:29,871
Well, uh...

710
00:33:29,939 --> 00:33:31,973
at least no one got hurt.

711
00:33:35,143 --> 00:33:37,744
It was a terrible color,
anyway.

712
00:33:37,812 --> 00:33:41,180
I-I'll get you a new one.

713
00:33:41,248 --> 00:33:42,782
Sorry.

714
00:33:53,321 --> 00:33:56,256
No traces of blood or D.N.A.
on the stolen car.

715
00:33:56,324 --> 00:33:59,259
Nothing?
So we have no murder weapon.
And no suspects.

716
00:33:59,327 --> 00:34:02,262
Let's start over. Go through
every witness statement.

717
00:34:02,330 --> 00:34:04,997
Excuse me. Hey, Cho.

718
00:34:05,065 --> 00:34:06,899
Oh, no.

719
00:34:06,966 --> 00:34:08,900
Oh, great.

720
00:34:08,968 --> 00:34:11,035
No. No,
you can handle this one.

721
00:34:11,103 --> 00:34:14,038
Just be sure to be clear
that the CBI is not liable.

722
00:34:14,106 --> 00:34:16,507
He is just a consultant.

723
00:34:19,211 --> 00:34:21,178
Uh, long story.

724
00:34:21,246 --> 00:34:23,279
Uh, I have to buy Walter
a new car.

725
00:34:23,347 --> 00:34:25,281
Could you show us
what you have?

726
00:34:25,348 --> 00:34:28,617
As I explained, Mr. Jane,
we need a bank statement

727
00:34:28,685 --> 00:34:31,921
to confirm--
Mr. Jane has assured me on his
honor that he's good for it.

728
00:34:31,989 --> 00:34:34,123
So I'll vouch for him.

729
00:34:34,191 --> 00:34:37,358
Do you need to see
<i>my</i> bank statement?
Of course not.

730
00:34:37,426 --> 00:34:39,460
All right.
Well, then let's do this.
Absolutely.

731
00:34:39,527 --> 00:34:41,029
I think we'll have Elias
show us around.

732
00:34:41,030 --> 00:34:42,530
But you want the best
to help show you around.

733
00:34:42,597 --> 00:34:46,800
Yes, he's second best.
He'll try harder.

734
00:34:46,868 --> 00:34:49,203
Right?
Right.

735
00:34:49,270 --> 00:34:51,271
Shall we?

736
00:34:56,745 --> 00:35:00,115
How about this one here?
Excellent eye. This car--

737
00:35:00,183 --> 00:35:04,391
Well, it's gray.
I mean, really? Gray?

738
00:35:04,459 --> 00:35:06,393
Your car.

739
00:35:06,461 --> 00:35:07,728
Mm.

740
00:35:07,796 --> 00:35:09,797
No.

741
00:35:09,865 --> 00:35:14,068
Gray'd be completely wrong,
wouldn't it?

742
00:35:14,136 --> 00:35:17,404
Let's take a look
at the, uh...

743
00:35:17,472 --> 00:35:20,174
Actually, no.
Let's go this way. Shall we?

744
00:35:24,979 --> 00:35:27,414
Patrick, we've been this way
before. Let's go back.

745
00:35:27,482 --> 00:35:29,917
Oh, please. Be patient.
See, the thing is, Walter,

746
00:35:29,985 --> 00:35:32,219
no matter how smart a plan
you make,

747
00:35:32,287 --> 00:35:35,222
there is always someone smarter
who will see through it--

748
00:35:35,290 --> 00:35:37,858
Makes it very hard
to get away with murder.

749
00:35:42,162 --> 00:35:45,231
I like this car shopping.
